Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into
1cm wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season
with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @Red Leicester{30%grams} and @mature Cheddar Cheese{40%grams}.
Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve. Quarter the
@baby plum tomatoes{125%grams}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{15%milliliter}, @olive oil{1/2%tbsp}
and a good pinch of @sugar{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{},
then stir in the tomatoes. Set aside to macerate.

Melt the @butter{20%grams} in a #small saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once melted, stir in the @plain flour{1.5%tbsp}. Cook until it forms a paste,
~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Stir in half the @vegetable stock paste{20%grams} and the @water{100%milliliter}
a little at a time.

Bring to the boil, then stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Stir in the @creme fraiche{75%grams} and add all the cheese. Keep stirring
until melted, then remove from the heat.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed. Cover with a
lid to keep warm and set aside.

Next, add the beans to a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Roughly mash half of them using a #potato masher{}. Stir in the @sugar{1%tsp}
and @water{75%milliliter}, @chipotle paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd prefer
things milder), @tomato puree{30%grams} and the remaining vegetable stock paste.
Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed. Remove from the
heat and cover with a lid to keep warm.

Just before the fries are ready, reheat the queso sauce or bean mixture if
needed. Add a splash of water if they've thickened.

Share the fries between your plates.

Top with the beans and drizzle over the queso sauce. Spoon over the salsa to
finish - fries loaded!

Enjoy!